CLICK HERE TO GET THE OPINION NEWSLETTER“When parents pack up the Christmas decorations, they tend to put away Christ as well,” he said.
“We tend to keep Christ in Christmas day alone.
Maybe it’s because we’re more prone to think that Christ came to give us laws to follow rather than life to the fullest?
The Apostle Paul also attests to the freedom from the weight of the law that Christ came to offer when he wrote, “So Christ has truly set us free.
I have overcome the world.” (John 16:33)To “Keep Christ in Christmas” is to miss out on the gifts Christ was born to give us.